==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swarf
<hw>Swarf</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Swerve</er>.]</ety> <def>To grow languid; to faint.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>swarf</xex> for very hunger.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swarf</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swarf
<hw>Swarf</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Swerve</er>.]</ety> <def>The
grit worn away from grindstones in grinding cutlery wet.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

